contentrichtext.text: {{Politics of the Netherlands}} '''General elections''' were held in the [[Netherlands]] on 11 June 1909.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] & Stöver, P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1395 ISBN 978-3-8329-5609-7</ref> The [[Anti Revolutionary Party]] and the [[General League of Roman Catholic Caucuses]] emerged as the largest parties, each winning 25 of the 100 seats in the [[House of Representatives of the Netherlands|House of Representatives]].<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p1412</ref> ==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Party !Votes !% !Seats !+/– |- |align=left|[[Anti Revolutionary Party]]||166,270||27.9||25||+10 |- |align=left|[[Liberal Union (Netherlands)|Liberal Union]]||106,086||17.8||20||– |- |align=left|[[Social Democratic Workers' Party (Netherlands)|Social Democratic Workers' Party]]||82,855||13.9||7||0 |- |align=left|[[General League of Roman Catholic Caucuses]]||76,087||13.9||25||0 |- |align=left|[[Christian Historical Union]]||63,306||10.6||10||+2 |- |align=left|[[Free-thinking Democratic League]]||54,007||9.1||9||–2 |- |align=left|[[League of Free Liberals|Liberal Democratic League]]||33,364||5.6||4||– |- |align=left|Other parties||13,985||2.3||0||0 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes|| ||–||–||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''596,060'''||'''100'''||'''100'''||'''0''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||843,487|| ||–||– |- |align=left colspan=5|Source: Nohlen & Stöver |} ==References== {{reflist}} {{Dutch general elections}} [[Category:General elections in the Netherlands|1909]] [[Category:1909 elections in Europe]] [[Category:1909 in the Netherlands]]
